			<div class="content" id="post-content-4861821">
									

<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[+]&nbsp;Overall</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[-]&nbsp;Overall</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The discovery section doesn't actually mention the SCP at all. Like, there's not even anything which like is referenced as a mandala or anything so it just kinda feels weird?</p>
<p>This means the addendum in the first iteration doesn't flow right because we haven't seen a SCP-XXXX mandala yet so there's not a clear thing that the dream team can like&#8230;do to go to SCP-XXXX-1?</p>
<p>The second iteration feels really unsatisfying as a whole: it feels like it doesn't quite build off the first one in a way that grants closure so much as is just kinda&#8230;confusing? Like, idk, I guess my question is why a SCP file for this anomaly exists but Dream Team aren't made aware of what Ara Orun are up to; or well, really, why the conflict between the two continues like why don't they just talk to each other? It's not like one of these files is more classified than the other, at least according to the ACS.</p>
<p>I like the first iteration generally; it feels lacking as a whole but it has some really nice 'descent into dreamland' vibes and I enjoy it; but iteration 2 doesn't really build off it so much as feel like it's the narrative equivalent of hitting a brick wall while you're going at 90 on the highway?</p>
<p>This said: it also feels a lot like this is a kinda generic dream entity and I'm not sure if that's just because I don't really get what's happening here on a metaphorical level?</p>
<hr />
<h3><span>Coherence</span></h3>
<p>Mostly fine; it feels like it's all kinda centred around a single thing and escalation situation and stuff; a few things I've mentioned above are a little iffy from this perspective too but they're relatively easily to fix.</p>
<h3><span>Consistency</span></h3>
<p>Not quite sure what you mean by this; but the internal logic of the piece feels like it's being kept consistent and the rules aren't suddenly changing or anything.</p>
<h3><span>Dialogue</span></h3>
<p>It's fine? There's not really any lines that stand out as being hugely memorable or anything; but there's equally no lines which feel hugely clunky or anything.</p>
<p>The characters could perhaps do with more of a personality: they're like, obviously different because of what they can do but they aren't all that different in terms of how they talk or what they're like as people.</p>
<h3><span>Clinical tone</span></h3>
<p>Yeah basically fine. See the LBL for some minor things.</p>
<h3><span>Pacing &amp; Plot &amp; Second list page</span></h3>
<p>See earlier comments.</p>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[-]&nbsp;Overall</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[+]&nbsp;Line&nbsp;By&nbsp;Line</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[-]&nbsp;Line&nbsp;By&nbsp;Line</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><em>Gonna note that I can miss stuff; flag things which are right as being wrong and indeed flag things which are deliberately wrong.</em><br />
<em>I'll likely use <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">strikethrough</span> to indicate stuff to remove and <span style="color: green">green text</span> to indicate stuff to add.</em></p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX and its related anomalies are undetectable by most individuals without sufficient anti-memetics training, therefore standard visual containment is not required.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>'related anomalies' feels vague here in an unsatisfying way: do you mean -1 and -2? do you mean a whole bunch of other antimemetic SCPs?</p>
<p>Also, I'm not necessarily sure that the lack of visual containment does necessarily follow here? Like I'm sure it does when a reader sees the actual properties and stuff; but in this isolated bit, it stands out as weird because like&#8230;we can still be affected by stuff we can't detect (e.g., if you drain all the air out a room, we might not be able to see that but we can certainly be affected by it).</p>
<p>This particularly feels janky when the next sentence implies it can be seen sometimes! So why don't they lock it up just in case?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>In rare circumstances, such as under the influence of psychedelics, visibility of SCP-XXXX is possible.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;In rare circumstances,&#8230;, SCP-XXXX can be visually detected.' would probably flow better: 'visibility' feels like a gradient rather than a binary, and possible feels iffy when talking gradients.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>are to be amnesticized and monitored <span style="color: green">for</span> any significant and abrupt changes</p>
</blockquote>
<p>'significant or abrupt' might be better here but but *shrugs*</p>
<blockquote>
<p>as well as <span style="color: green">for</span> signs of psychosis</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX Is an anomalous mandala</p>
</blockquote>
<p>rogue capital</p>
<blockquote>
<p>a graphic and often symbolic pattern usually in the form of a circle divided into four separate sections or bearing a multiple projection of an image.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>'bearing a multiple projection of an image' is janky but I'm not exactly sure how best to fix it</p>
<p>I would also generally lean towards capitalising the first word of a footnote.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>that has been observed appearing in multiple population centers.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I feel like this is a touch vague about what it actually is? Like is it just&#8230;an image that appears a lot in posters? Is it a weird 2d image entity that moves around?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Every instance of SCP-XXXX is identical in pattern, coloration and size.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>this feels a little unsatisfying because it's never actually like, described in any way: like I get putting an image of it in the file is probably a bad idea but like&#8230;there's not even a vague description of what it includes.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX-2 is an entity of varying form that is located in SCP-XXXX-1. Its form is that a young <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">humanoid</span> woman with wings on its back that resemble those of a blue butterfly. (<em>Blue Morpho</em>)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Does it have varying form or is it's form that of a young woman with wings on its back that resemble those of a blue butterfly?</p>
<p>IMO: you can cut humanoid here; if you say 'young woman', people will assume 'human' or at least 'human adjacent'.</p>
<p>I'd also have the 'blue morpho' before the full stop; or potentially as the main text with a footnote explaining it's a butterfly</p>
<blockquote>
<p>MTF Omicron Rho (&quot;The Dream Team&quot;) discovered SCP-XXXX-2 in their deployment into SCP-XXXX-1. See addenda.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'd probably cut this since the conflation between this and the discovery right after feels&#8230;confusing? Like in the sense that this introduces a second discovery event right before you introduce the first.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>When the congregation underwent substantial changes in behavior while the parishioners were in prayer.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is a sentence fragment that's missing what happened when said substantial changes occurred.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Another significant portion of the congregation attempted</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I feel like specifying an approximate number instead of 'significant' would be more effective here.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>to eat portions of the marble pews<sup><span style="color: red">3</span></sup> Traces of blood and fragments of broken teeth were discovered at the site of this incident.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>this footnote is unnecessary and you're missing a period.</p>
<p>I also feel like the flow of information is weird: I think noting that it's hypothesised that people tried to eat the pews based of the blood/teeth fragments at the site would work better; or like, indicating that the eating caused there to be said traces left or something.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>After this incident, the Foundation dispatched field agents to survey the surroundings</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This phrasing kinda implies that the Foundation knew about the incident in some magical manner and immediately dispatched agents after it occurred; it feels like this needs an intermediate step like e.g. embedded agents in the police department diverting this to the foundation or something.</p>
<p>I'd also be tempted to put a number of agents in here; or refer to a single field agent say.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Their comms devices were discovered drenched in a<span style="text-decoration: line-through;">n unseen</span> fluid that could only be detected by Foundation psychics.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This feels weird to me; like, the further in we get, the less saying they were discovered 'drenched' feels like it makes sense. Also 'unseen' is unnecessary if only psychics can detect it; it implies it could be e.g. felt whereas the later part indicates it can't even be felt.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Exploration Video Log Transcript</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'd probably trim the 'exploration team' and 'subject' fields and instead add a short summary of the purpose of this: like, why are Omicron Rho being sent in? Is their job 'to identify anomalies within SCP-XXXX-1' or 'to explore -1' or 'to recover someone from -1' or?</p>
<blockquote>
<p><em>Dream Team moves toward locked wooden door.</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>IMO: not having a 'The' at the start here feels a little wonky.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>House, Hero and Operator lean against the wall next to the door.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Listing the names like this implies there's more team members than just those three here</p>
<blockquote>
<p>They slowly open the door and peer through the crack.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This was described as a 'locked wooden door' a second earlier; how are they opening it now?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The nun walks over to the door and opens it.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>What door is this? The only one mentioned has already been opened?</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;"><strong>Operator:</strong></span> <em>&lt;Operator takes several pictures of the fluid and saves them to her folder.&gt;</em></p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>FOOTAGE LOST</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'd probably centre this</p>
<blockquote>
<p><em>&lt;Operator slowly approaches a sedated young woman.</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Missing the &gt; at the end here</p>
<blockquote>
<p>save for a Mandala symbol that appears tattooed onto its face</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Is this a SCP-XXXX mandala or a different mandala?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>//&lt;Hero turns around, telekinetically lifts chunks of dirt and rocks out of the ground and throwing them into the distance.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Missing the closing &gt; and //</p>
<p>This action, and the following stuff, feels&#8230;completely disconnected from what was happening just before it in a slightly unsatisfying way</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Dream Team appears in what resembles medieval Europe</p>
</blockquote>
<p>'appears somewhere that resembles' might parse better here</p>
<blockquote>
<p>House: &lt;Erects a brick wall from the ground, stopping a citizen who was mid-flight.&gt;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>IMO: cut the dialogue tag and just use the action but with 'House' at the start.</p>
<p>Then again, this just&#8230;feels odd for House to do?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Operator pulls House by the collar of his fatigues and pulls him backwards.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'd change the first 'pulls' to 'grabs', or cut the 'and pulls him' and move 'backwards' to just after 'House'.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>House's leg gets caught in the serpent's form,</p>
</blockquote>
<p>How does it get caught? This feels weirdly passive</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Operator: &lt;Operator continues dragging House.&gt;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Probably the last time I'll mention this but the dialogue tag can be cut here and anywhere you do this.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>launching every citizen around him.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>this feels like it's missing something like 'into the air' at the end; like, words indicating where the citizens go, y'know?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Hero frees himself from the large man's hold</p>
</blockquote>
<p>this feels weirdly lacking in description of how it's done</p>
<blockquote>
<p>standing underneath an instance of SCP-XXXX.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>this is altogether far too far into this SCP for this to be the first explicitly mentioned instance of SCP-XXXX (there's been a few mandalas that could be the scp but nothing concrete)</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&lt;SCP-XXXX-2 steps back and stares at the stone circle.&gt;//</p>
</blockquote>
<p>missing opening //</p>
<blockquote>
<p>FOOTAGE LOST</p>
</blockquote>
<p>the last one in the document is missing the lines before/after it.</p>
<hr />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h3><span>Iteration 1</span></h3>
</div>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<p>Mobile Task Force Omega-0 (&quot;Ará Orún&quot;) is to be deployed into SCP-XXXX-1 by using SCP-XXXX as entryways.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>deployed into -1 to do what?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX-3 is to be forcibly contained within SCP-XXXX-1 and redirected back into SCP-XXXX-2.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Something about the flow of this feels janky; but I think it's just that we haven't had the new -1 and -2 established so -2 being a thing that exists in -1 isn't like,,, something we're sure of yet?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>All efforts are to be focused on a permanent solution to SCP-XXXX-2's rapidly deteroriating condition.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I feel like something more specific than 'rapidly deteriorating condition' would be good here: really show what's happening in an evocative way, y'know?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Its primary locations for spawning include but are not limited to</p>
</blockquote>
<p>something about this feels iffy; maybe &quot;It primarily appears in the following locations:&quot; would be better?</p>
<blockquote>
<ul>
<li>Mass congregations.</li>
<li>Cults.</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p>These feel&#8230;vague for locations?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX is the pathway between SCP-XXXX-1 and reality.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>My general feeling is that you have to say what -1 is before you can say this; perhaps saing e.g. &quot;pathway between the collective unconsciousness (designated SCP-XXXX-1) and reality&quot; would be best?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Addendum:</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I would add line breaks between the paragraphs here just to space it out a little.</p>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[-]&nbsp;Line&nbsp;By&nbsp;Line</a></div>
</div>
</div>

